# Cursor Rules for Grandfield Media
## Astro + Vercel + Multi-Site Monorepo

## Project Architecture

This is a **multi-site monorepo** using pnpm workspaces. Each niche has its own independent Astro site, all deployed separately to Vercel.

### Directory Structure
```
grandfield-media/
├── sites/
│   ├── grandfieldmedia/          # Main brand site
│   ├── business-entrepreneurship/
│   ├── career-professional/
│   ├── events-celebrations/
│   ├── health-wellness/
│   ├── home-lifestyle/
│   └── [other-niche-sites]/
├── packages/                      # Shared code (utilities, components, types)
│   ├── shared-ui/
│   ├── shared-utils/
│   └── [other-packages]/
├── package.json                   # Root workspace config
├── pnpm-workspace.yaml           # Workspace definition
└── pnpm-lock.yaml               # Dependency lock
```

## Each Site Structure

Each site in `sites/` follows this pattern:

```
sites/[site-name]/
├── src/
│   ├── components/               # Reusable Astro components
│   ├── layouts/                  # Page layouts (Base, etc)
│   ├── pages/                    # Route definitions
│   ├── styles/                   # Global & component styles
│   ├── lib/                      # Utilities & helpers
│   └── assets/                   # Images, icons, etc
├── public/                       # Static assets
├── astro.config.mjs              # Astro config (Tailwind integration)
├── tailwind.config.js            # Tailwind config
├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript config (strict mode)
└── package.json                  # Site-specific dependencies
```

## Tech Stack

- **Astro** 4.0.0 — Static site generation
- **Tailwind CSS** 3.4.0 — Utility-first styling
- **TypeScript** — Strict mode enabled
- **pnpm** 11.10.0+ — Package manager with workspaces
- **Vercel** — Deployment platform (per-site deployment)

## Astro Best Practices

### Component Structure
```astro
---
// Use TypeScript for props
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
}

const { title, description, variant = 'primary' } = Astro.props;
// Import utilities
import { formatDate } from '@/lib/utils';
---

<section class={`section section--${variant}`}>
  <h2>{title}</h2>
  {description && <p>{description}</p>}
</section>

<style scoped>
  /* Component-scoped CSS */
  .section {
    @apply p-4;
  }
  .section--primary {
    @apply bg-blue-500 text-white;
  }
  .section--secondary {
    @apply bg-gray-200 text-black;
  }
</style>
```

### Using Path Aliases
- Import with `@/` prefix (maps to `src/`)
- Examples:
  ```astro
  import Button from '@/components/Button.astro';
  import { getMetadata } from '@/lib/seo';
  import type { Post } from '@/lib/types';
  ```

### File Organization Best Practices
- **pages/** — One `.astro` file per route (file-based routing)
- **components/** — Reusable UI components
- **layouts/** — Wrap pages with consistent structure
- **lib/** — Utilities (`utils.ts`), helpers, constants, types
- **styles/** — Only global styles; prefer scoped Tailwind
- **assets/** — Images, logos, icons

### Dynamic Routes
- Use `[slug].astro` for dynamic pages
- Implement `getStaticPaths()` for static generation:
  ```ts
  export async function getStaticPaths() {
    const posts = await getAllPosts();
    return posts.map(post => ({
      params: { slug: post.slug },
      props: { post }
    }));
  }
  ```

## Tailwind CSS Integration

### Configuration
- Each site has its own `tailwind.config.js`
- Integrated via `@astrojs/tailwind`
- Tailwind is scoped to `src/` directory only

### Styling Approach
- **Prefer Tailwind utilities** over custom CSS when possible
- Use `@apply` for component-specific Tailwind combos
- Keep scoped component styles minimal
- Global styles only in `src/styles/globals.css`

### Common Patterns
```astro
<!-- Tailwind in className -->
<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-600">
  Click me
</button>

<!-- Using @apply for repeated combinations -->
<style>
  .btn-primary {
    @apply px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-600;
  }
</style>
```

## Monorepo Workflow

### Package Manager Commands
```bash
# Root level
pnpm install                          # Install all dependencies
pnpm run dev                          # Start all sites (if root script)

# Per-site operations
pnpm --filter business-entrepreneurship run dev
pnpm --filter business-entrepreneurship run build
pnpm --filter business-entrepreneurship run preview

# Install dep in a specific site
pnpm --filter business-entrepreneurship add [package-name]

# Install dev dep in a specific site
pnpm --filter business-entrepreneurship add -D [package-name]

# Add to shared package
pnpm --filter @grandfield/shared-ui add [package-name]
```

### Key pnpm Flags
- `--filter [workspace]` — Target specific workspace
- `-D` or `--save-dev` — Add as dev dependency
- `-w` or `--workspace-root` — Add to root workspace
- `--shared-workspace-lockfile` — Use workspace-wide lock file (default)

## Shared Code

### Location: `packages/` Directory
- **shared-ui/** — Reusable Astro components
- **shared-utils/** — Utility functions & helpers
- Create new packages for common functionality

### Importing from Shared
```astro
// From a site, import from shared package
import { Button, Card } from '@grandfield/shared-ui';
import { formatDate, slugify } from '@grandfield/shared-utils';
```

## TypeScript Configuration

### Base Configuration
Each site extends `astro/tsconfigs/strict` with:
- `jsxImportSource: "astro"` — Use Astro for JSX
- `strictNullChecks: true` — Strict null checking
- Path aliases via `@/*` → `src/*`

### Type Safety
- Always use TypeScript interfaces for component props
- Export types from shared packages
- Run `tsc --noEmit` to check types before deploy

## Vercel Deployment

### Per-Site Deployment
Each site deploys independently. Set up Vercel projects for:
- `grandfieldmedia.com`
- `business-entrepreneurship-[domain]`
- `career-professional-[domain]`
- etc.

### Configuration
For each Vercel project (no `vercel.json` needed if using defaults):

**Build Command:**
```bash
pnpm --filter [site-name] run build
```

**Output Directory:**
```
sites/[site-name]/dist
```

**Environment Variables:**
- Set in Vercel project settings
- Use `PUBLIC_` prefix for public env vars
- Access via `import.meta.env.PUBLIC_*` in Astro

### Sample vercel.json (create per site if needed)
```json
{
  "buildCommand": "pnpm --filter business-entrepreneurship run build",
  "outputDirectory": "sites/business-entrepreneurship/dist",
  "env": [
    "PUBLIC_API_URL",
    "PUBLIC_SITE_NAME"
  ]
}
```

## Development Workflow

### Starting Development
```bash
# For a specific site
cd sites/[site-name]
pnpm run dev

# OR from root (if you add root dev script)
pnpm --filter [site-name] run dev
```

### Development Best Practices
1. **One terminal per site** — Each site runs on different port
2. **Astro Hot Reload** — Changes auto-refresh in browser
3. **TypeScript Checking** — Run `tsc --noEmit` before committing
4. **Build Locally First** — Test `pnpm run build` before pushing

## Code Standards

### Naming Conventions
- **Components:** `PascalCase.astro` → `Button.astro`, `HeroSection.astro`
- **Files/folders:** `kebab-case` → `src/components/nav-header/`
- **Functions/utils:** `camelCase` → `formatDate()`, `getPostData()`
- **Constants:** `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` → `API_BASE_URL`, `MAX_ITEMS`
- **Types/interfaces:** `PascalCase` → `type Post`, `interface Props`

### Commit Messages
Use conventional commits format:
```
type(scope): description

type: feat, fix, docs, refactor, style, perf, test, chore
scope: which site or package (e.g., "business-entrepreneurship", "shared-ui")
description: what changed, why it changed

Examples:
- feat(business-entrepreneurship): add hero section component
- fix(career-professional): resolve nav menu alignment
- refactor(shared-ui): extract button styles to tailwind
- docs: update README with deployment steps
```

### Comments & Documentation
- Use JSDoc for functions with multiple parameters
- Comment complex logic inline
- Keep each site's README updated
- Document decisions in git commit messages

## Git Workflow

### Branch Strategy
```
main                 # Production-ready
├── feature/[description]     # New features
├── fix/[description]         # Bug fixes
├── refactor/[description]    # Code improvements
└── docs/[description]        # Documentation
```

### Before Committing
```bash
# Type check
tsc --noEmit

# Optional: lint (if eslint configured)
pnpm run lint

# Test build for the site you modified
pnpm --filter [site-name] run build
```

### Deployment via Vercel
1. Push to main
2. Each site auto-deploys via Vercel (one project per site)
3. Check preview deployments on PRs
4. Production deployment on main merge

## Performance Optimization

### Bundle & Build
- **Minimize JS** — Astro ships zero JS by default (keep it that way)
- **Use Islands Architecture** — Only hydrate interactive components
- **Image Optimization** — Use Astro's `<Image />` component
- **CSS Efficiency** — Tailwind auto-purges unused styles

### Caching Strategies (Vercel)
- Static files cache indefinitely (`.js`, `.css`, `.woff2`)
- HTML pages cache 1 hour default (configure via headers)
- Set cache headers for different asset types in `vercel.json` if needed

### Monitoring
- Check Vercel Analytics for Core Web Vitals
- Monitor Lighthouse scores in CI if configured
- Profile build times: `pnpm --filter [site] run build` locally

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

**Build Fails Locally but Passes Tests**
- Clear cache: `rm -rf dist/ node_modules/.vite`
- Rebuild: `pnpm install && pnpm --filter [site] run build`

**Astro Not Recognizing Changes**
- Restart dev server: `Ctrl+C`, then `pnpm run dev` again
- Clear Astro cache: `rm -rf .astro/`

**TypeScript Errors in Editor**
- Ensure `astro/tsconfigs/strict` is extended in `tsconfig.json`
- Restart VS Code/Cursor
- Run `pnpm install` to sync types

**Tailwind Classes Not Applying**
- Verify `tailwind.config.js` has correct `content` paths
- Restart dev server
- Check scoped styles don't override Tailwind

**Dependency Issues**
- Clear lock file and reinstall: `rm pnpm-lock.yaml && pnpm install`
- Check pnpm version: `pnpm -v` (should be 11.10.0+)

## Quick Reference

### Essential Commands
```bash
# Development
pnpm --filter [site] run dev           # Start dev server
pnpm --filter [site] run build         # Build for production
pnpm --filter [site] run preview       # Preview production build

# Management
pnpm install                           # Install all deps
pnpm update                            # Update deps
pnpm --filter [site] add [package]    # Add dependency to site
pnpm store prune                       # Clean pnpm cache

# Utilities
tsc --noEmit                           # Type check
pnpm --filter [site] run build --stats # Build with stats
```

### Path Aliases
- `@/*` → `src/*` (use for all imports within a site)

### Key Files Per Site
- `astro.config.mjs` — Astro configuration
- `tailwind.config.js` — Tailwind configuration
- `tsconfig.json` — TypeScript configuration
- `src/pages/` — Routes
- `src/components/` — Reusable components
- `src/layouts/` — Page layouts

## Deployment Checklist

- [ ] Run type check: `tsc --noEmit`
- [ ] Build locally: `pnpm --filter [site] run build`
- [ ] Preview: `pnpm --filter [site] run preview`
- [ ] Commit with conventional message
- [ ] Push to feature branch
- [ ] Create PR, test Vercel preview
- [ ] Merge to main → Auto-deploys to Vercel
- [ ] Verify production at site domain

